    As we know,

    There are known knowns.

    There are things

    We know we know.

    We also know

    There are known unknowns.

    That is to say

    We know there are some things

    We do not know.

    But there are also unknown unknowns,

    The ones we don't know

    We don't know.

-- Donald Rumsfeld, Feb. 12, 2002, Department of Defense news briefing
